I"O<p>In trading jargon, <strong>ATH</strong> stands for <strong>All-Time High</strong>.</p>

<p>A market makes a new all-time high if its price action rises above the previous all-time maximum price. There is no other requirement for timeframe, <a href="/glossary/pattern-trading/">patterns</a> or any special <a href="/technical-analysis/">technical setup</a>. Even if the market retraces abruptly, the new ATH still counts.</p>

<h3 id="the-bitcoin-ath">The Bitcoin ATH</h3>

<p>On the bitcoin-dollar market, an ATH will happen when the price rises to anywhere over 20k USD.</p>

<h3 id="ath-jargon-term">ATH jargon term</h3>

<p>ATH is a term that you will find used in legacy trading as well, it is not specific to crypto.</p>

